---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="FAQ - Frequently Asked Questions"
  description="Find answers to frequently asked questions about Resize-It. Learn about image processing, privacy, and supported formats."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <div class="bg-white text-center font-crimson mt-[80px] md:mt-10">
    <h1 class="text-[40px] md:text-[50px] leading-tight">  
      Frequently Asked
      <span class="text-primary">Questions</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-lg md:text-xl mt-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4">
      Quick answers to questions you may have about our tools and services.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Categories -->
  <div class="mt-12 px-5 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <p class="text-primary font-crimson text-lg mb-3">
      Browse Topics
    </p>
    <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[50px] mb-6">
      Find Your Answer
    </h2>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Sections -->
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-6 md:py-8 space-y-8">
    
    <!-- General Questions -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] mb-6 text-gray-900">General Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">What is Resize-It?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Resize-It is a free, browser-based suite of image processing tools. We provide professional-quality image resizing, compression, format conversion, and passport photo creation—all without requiring uploads to our servers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Is Resize-It really free?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Yes, completely free! There are no hidden fees, subscriptions, or premium tiers. All features are available to everyone at no cost.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Do I need to create an account?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            No account is needed. Simply visit our website and start using any tool immediately. We believe in keeping things simple and accessible.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">What browsers are supported?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Resize-It works on all modern browsers including Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge. We recommend using the latest version of your preferred browser for the best experience.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Privacy & Security -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] mb-6 text-gray-900">Privacy & Security</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Are my images uploaded to your servers?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            No. All image processing happens entirely in your browser using JavaScript. Your images never leave your device, ensuring complete privacy and security.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Do you store or track my images?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Absolutely not. We don't store, track, or have any access to your images. Since processing happens locally in your browser, your images remain completely private.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Is it safe to process sensitive images?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Yes, it's completely safe. Because all processing happens on your device, you can confidently process confidential documents, personal photos, or any sensitive images.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Image Processing -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] mb-6 text-gray-900">Image Processing</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">What image formats are supported?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            We support JPEG, PNG, WebP, and most common image formats as input. You can convert between JPEG, PNG, and WebP formats.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Is there a file size limit?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Since processing happens in your browser, the limit depends on your device's memory. Most modern devices can handle images up to 50-100MB without issues.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Will I lose image quality?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Quality depends on your settings. When resizing, we use high-quality algorithms. For compression, you control the quality level. Converting to lossless formats like PNG preserves all quality.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Can I process multiple images at once?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Currently, our tools process one image at a time to ensure the best quality and performance. However, you can quickly process multiple images sequentially.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Passport Photos -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] mb-6 text-gray-900">Passport Photos</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Which countries are supported?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            We have pre-configured dimensions for US, UK, India, EU, and many other countries. You can also enter custom dimensions for any country not listed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">How many photos fit on one page?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            This depends on the photo size and paper size. The tool automatically calculates and shows you how many photos will fit on your selected paper size (typically 8-12 photos on A4/Letter).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">What resolution are the passport photos?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            All passport photos are generated at 300 DPI (dots per inch), which is the professional printing standard and meets official passport photo requirements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Can I use these for official applications?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Yes, our tool creates photos that meet official size requirements. However, please ensure your photo itself (lighting, background, expression) meets your country's specific passport photo guidelines.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Technical Questions -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[40px] mb-6 text-gray-900">Technical Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Do I need an internet connection?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            You need an internet connection to load the website initially. However, once loaded, the image processing works offline since it happens in your browser.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Why is processing slow on my device?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Processing speed depends on your device's capabilities and the image size. Large images may take longer on older devices. For best performance, use a modern device and optimize very large images first.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-crimson text-xl font-medium mb-3 text-gray-900">Can I use Resize-It on mobile?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Yes! Resize-It is fully responsive and works on mobile devices. However, for the best experience with large images or complex operations, we recommend using a desktop or tablet.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Still Have Questions Section -->
  <div class="mt-16 px-5 max-w-7xl mx-auto mb-16">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tertiary to-green-50 border-2 border-secondary/30 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-crimson text-[30px] md:text-[50px] mb-4">
        Still Have Questions?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg mb-6">
        Can't find the answer you're looking for? We're here to help.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-tertiary hover:bg-primary text-primary hover:text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-3xl font-crimson font-semibold transition-all duration-700 ease-in-out">
          Contact Support
        </a>
        <a href="/help" class="inline-block bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 text-primary border-2 border-primary px-6 py-3 rounded-3xl font-crimson font-semibold transition-all duration-300">
          Visit Help Center
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>
